1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,670
[Marcus] As long as those bastards
protecting the syndicate

2
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:06,381
are roaming freely here inside the NLEA,

3
00:00:06,464 --> 00:00:07,882
no one is truly safe.

4
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:09,175
There's someone in the upper ranks
on our side.

5
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:10,885
You can't trust anyone
so easily these days.

6
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:13,722
[Maya] <i>According to Datu Rahman Abubakar,</i>

7
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:16,516
<i>those behind the massacre</i>
<i>are from the NLEA.</i>

8
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:20,854
[woman] <i>Did someone from the NLEA</i>
<i>really kill Patrick?</i>

9
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:24,274
[Marcus] I won't let their deaths
go unpunished.

10
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:25,942
Before, I only had to spy on Marcus,

11
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:28,528
but now even Espina's up to something.

12
00:00:28,611 --> 00:00:31,614
[Felix] Do you think he knows
where Jalil Abubakar is hiding?

13
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,159
[man] <i>Sir, that's where</i>
<i>Datu Rahman was picked up</i>

14
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:36,119
<i>by the cop wearing glasses earlier.</i>

15
00:00:36,202 --> 00:00:37,954
[Jamilah] Doc Teresa,
what are you doing here?

16
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,247
I just wanted to check on you.

17
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,750
[Maya, in English] <i>This island</i>
<i>used to be full of life.</i>

18
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:44,169
<i>But now, it has become a graveyard,</i>

19
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:46,296
<i>with so many buried around.</i>

20
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:50,759
<i>And the victims,</i>
<i>along with their families,</i>

21
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,886
<i>only have one wish… justice.</i>

22
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:55,346
[Jamilah] <i>They're my friends, Doc Teresa.</i>

23
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:58,141
We've been together since childhood.

24
00:00:58,224 --> 00:00:59,893
Jamilah, I'll be gone for a while.

25
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,144
Where are you going?

26
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:02,353
I'm going back to the island.

27
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:05,398
[Jalil] <i>Father wants me</i>
<i>to check on our community.</i>

28
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:06,608
[Jamilah] <i>I'll go with you!</i>

29
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:09,319
[Jalil] <i>I'll be able</i>
<i>to move faster if I'm alone.</i>

30
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:17,035
[mysterious theme music playing]

31
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:25,835
BLOOD VS DUTY

32
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:29,672
Doc Teresa, you really
didn't have to come.

33
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,925
[chuckles softly] It's okay, Jamilah.

34
00:01:32,008 --> 00:01:33,426
[Omar] Doc Teresa.

35
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,094
- Oh, Omar.
- [chuckles] Doc Teresa.

36
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:36,679
What brings you here?

37
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:39,974
Yeah. I just visited Jamilah.

38
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:42,143
I'm glad you dropped by.

39
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:44,354
I'm sorry I couldn't visit you.

40
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:48,316
I just wanted to see how Jamilah is doing.

41
00:01:48,399 --> 00:01:50,110
It's okay, Doc Teresa.

42
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,946
Don't worry, Doc Teresa.

43
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:55,490
- I'll go to work tomorrow.
- [gentle music playing]

44
00:01:55,573 --> 00:01:57,075
Thank you again.

45
00:01:57,158 --> 00:01:58,243
Be careful, okay?

46
00:01:58,326 --> 00:01:59,869
I'll see you at the hospital.

47
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,621
- [Jamilah] Okay, Doc Teresa.
- Bye, Doc Teresa.

48
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:03,832
- Take care.
- You take care too.

49
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:08,294
[gentle music playing]

50
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:18,388
[engine starting]

51
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:25,311
[unsettling music playing]

52
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:40,451
[seatbelt unbuckling]

53
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:43,454
[unsettling music continues]

54
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,128
[Felix] <i>What is Marcus's mother</i>
<i>doing here?</i>

55
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:56,885
<i>Why does she seem</i>
<i>so important in this place?</i>

56
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,808
- It's crazy, Mama Loi.
- What's crazy?

57
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:07,604
What happened in Damai Island.

58
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:09,647
- Ah. Yeah.
- Remember?

59
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:13,401
That news really broke my heart back then.

60
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:17,322
I also heard about the survivors.

61
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:19,699
I can't imagine how hard it must've been

62
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:21,159
to lose your loved ones.

63
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:23,161
- You're right about that.
- [tutting] Whoo!

64
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:26,039
I mean, the residents there
were minding their own business…

65
00:03:26,122 --> 00:03:26,956
Oh?

66
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:30,585
…and living quiet, peaceful lives,

67
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:32,503
then they got attacked?

68
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,297
My God, exactly.

69
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:39,052
Kids, women, no one was spared!

70
00:03:40,511 --> 00:03:45,016
Gosh, that's why I don't like
talking about things like that.

71
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:47,018
- They make me cry.
- [Ogie] Oh.

72
00:03:47,101 --> 00:03:49,479
I just want to talk about happy things!

73
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:50,647
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

74
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,357
Seriously, Mrena?

75
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,484
You want them to adjust
so you won't end up crying?

76
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:55,401
[Ogie chuckles]

77
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:59,656
<i>So, has everyone watched</i>
<i>MMK's documentary?</i>

78
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:02,075
<i>My goodness, I had no idea</i>
<i>the people in Damai Island</i>

79
00:04:02,158 --> 00:04:03,326
<i>went through all that.</i>

80
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:06,913
<i>You know, it's true that you'll</i>
<i>never really understand</i>

81
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:08,289
<i>what other people are going through</i>

82
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:11,251
<i>until you see it with your own eyes.</i>

83
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:14,545
<i>And now that the tragedy on the island</i>

84
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:16,798
<i>has finally been given a face,</i>

85
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:22,720
<i>hopefully, justice for the people there</i>
<i>will come much sooner.</i>

86
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:25,098
<i>I hope things will move faster now.</i>

87
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:26,182
<i>Please!</i>

88
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,810
[In Arabic] Praise be to God!

89
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:33,147
Thank you so much, Maya Mae Kalaw,

90
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:37,360
for making a documentary
about the massacre.

91
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:40,530
<i>Because of it, people are still</i>
<i>talking about what happened,</i>

92
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:43,366
<i>instead of just brushing it aside.</i>

93
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:47,620
<i>It made people aware of the suffering</i>

94
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:49,998
<i>our community went through.</i>

95
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:52,041
<i>So, Maya Mae Kalaw,</i>

96
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:55,169
<i>thank you from the bottom of my heart.</i>

97
00:04:55,712 --> 00:04:59,132
It is also important
to be aware of these things.

98
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:01,884
We can't just talk
about happy things all the time.

99
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:03,886
There has to be a balance.

100
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:06,848
We need to be aware
of what others are going through,

101
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:09,517
even though we don't always
get to interact,

102
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:13,187
so we can better understand them.

103
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:16,566
So, to the residents of Damai Island,

104
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:22,780
we pray that you get justice
for what happened to you.

105
00:05:22,864 --> 00:05:23,698
That's right.

106
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:29,370
[Marcus sighs]

107
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,543
Son, how are you?

108
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:36,919
[sighs]

109
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:41,466
[Teresa] I watched Maya Mae Kalaw's
documentary about the island.

110
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:43,760
So, Datu Rahman has surrendered?

111
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:48,097
Espina took him to headquarters.

112
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,143
Datu Rahman surrendered to him.

113
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:55,063
- Really?
- [deep breath]

114
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,065
To Allan?

115
00:05:57,148 --> 00:05:59,942
[pensive music playing]

116
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:00,860
Allan?

117
00:06:01,944 --> 00:06:03,613
You call him by his first name?

118
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:05,364
Are you close with him?

119
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:10,161
When you went to the island,

120
00:06:10,244 --> 00:06:12,455
I took Allan home with me.

121
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:17,293
[in English] Okay… [scoffs]

122
00:06:17,376 --> 00:06:19,003
- Here at home?
- [Teresa] Yes.

123
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:21,089
I forgot to tell you.

124
00:06:22,256 --> 00:06:24,092
My car broke down.

125
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:29,388
I tried calling you, but my phone died.

126
00:06:29,972 --> 00:06:34,060
Luckily, Allan came to my aid.

127
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:37,772
So I invited him here for dinner
as a thank you.

128
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:39,315
[in English] Wow.

129
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:41,567
Really?

130
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:42,568
Why?

131
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:45,780
Remember that show-off
rookie cop at the office

132
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:48,950
that I told you about?

133
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,035
That's him. Allan.

134
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:53,579
[chuckles]

135
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,166
Maybe you haven't really
gotten to know him yet.

136
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:01,879
[pensive music continues]

137
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:05,341
Reyes, I know you hid Datu Rahman.

138
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:10,054
I know you helped him escape Zylverix.

139
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:10,972
‪[dramatic sting]

140
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:13,099
Thank you.

141
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:17,728
Don't worry.

142
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:20,606
I understand why you did that, Reyes.

143
00:07:21,315 --> 00:07:22,650
I won't tell anyone.

144
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,902
It'll be our secret.

145
00:07:24,986 --> 00:07:28,281
[pensive music continues]

146
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,032
[Jalil] <i>Thank you.</i>

147
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:38,249
Maybe you're right.

148
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,962
He could be a good guy.

149
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:45,423
- [sighs]
- We had a chat.

150
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:51,179
He opened up to me
about some personal matters.

151
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:55,308
What did he say?

152
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:57,518
That's just between us.

153
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:00,104
[scoffs]

154
00:08:00,188 --> 00:08:02,565
[Marcus] You're keeping secrets
from me now?

155
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:04,650
For Allan?

156
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:07,153
In case you forgot, I'm your son.

157
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:09,822
[chuckles] Goodness, are you jealous?

158
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:12,825
[pensive music continues]

159
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:15,244
[sighs]

160
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:17,246
You might even start calling him your son.

161
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,168
Take care, son.

162
00:08:22,251 --> 00:08:25,004
[pensive music playing]

163
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,009
You too.

164
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,767
Oh, come on,
you're being silly. Let's eat.

165
00:08:38,601 --> 00:08:41,270
Just eat, okay? Enough of that. Sit down.

166
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:43,648
- Sit down and eat, son.
- [guttural sigh]

167
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:51,197
[gentle music playing]

168
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,377
NATIONAL LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY

169
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,711
NATIONAL LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY

170
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,881
[in English] The situation
is getting out of hand!

171
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:12,802
[unsettling music playing]

172
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,556
- [in English] Sir.
- [in English] Carry on.

173
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:20,434
So, how's the investigation going?

174
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,273
Still nothing?!

175
00:09:26,524 --> 00:09:28,943
NLEA has become a laughing stock.

176
00:09:29,026 --> 00:09:32,697
Our trust rating is at an all-time low.

177
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:36,242
People are saying that
we're protecting the culprit

178
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:37,410
because he's one of us!

179
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:38,953
They've lost trust in us!

180
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:47,211
I need to know
who is responsible for all of this.

181
00:09:50,214 --> 00:09:52,383
- Colonel Paulino.
- [in English] Yes, sir.

182
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:53,759
[in English] Can I count on you?

183
00:09:53,843 --> 00:09:55,303
Sure, sir. I'll handle it.

184
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:56,887
[in English] Good.

185
00:09:56,971 --> 00:09:59,807
[unsettling music continues]

186
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:01,559
‪[door clicks shut]

187
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:12,194
- Dionisio.
- [Dionisio] <i>General.</i>

188
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:16,532
General Villanueva believes
that Datu Rahman is telling the truth,

189
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:20,786
that the syndicate's protector
is from NLEA.

190
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:22,872
[exhales sharply]

191
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,874
Relax, Dionisio.

192
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:26,709
I'll take care of it.

193
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:33,507
[discordant music playing]

194
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:37,386
What are we going to do, General?

195
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:39,347
[Manuel chuckles]

196
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:41,474
Well…

197
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:47,271
We're going to give them what they need.

198
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:54,278
We'll give them someone
who can take the fall.

199
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:58,115
[chuckles]

200
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:07,083
Sir, are you saying that Datu Rahman
is telling the truth?

201
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,502
Do you believe he is innocent

202
00:11:09,585 --> 00:11:12,922
and that something
is going on here in NLEA?

203
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:16,550
Sir, I'm sorry to ask, but… [sighs]

204
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:19,053
What changed your mind?

205
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:21,931
Why do you believe
in Datu Rahman all of a sudden?

206
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:24,558
You didn't even believe
in Marcus last time.

207
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:27,853
[in English] What changed?

208
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:31,690
I mean, based on official evidence,

209
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:33,651
Datu Rahman is still a criminal.

210
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,324
The accusations against
Datu Rahman are not true.

211
00:11:42,284 --> 00:11:44,495
Sir, how can you be sure?

212
00:11:45,287 --> 00:11:46,997
Ever since Marcus came back
from his leave,

213
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:47,998
you've also changed.

214
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:51,043
What's going on?
Do you know something that I don't?

215
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:53,587
I want to understand.

216
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:55,339
[Lara scoffs]

217
00:11:55,423 --> 00:12:02,138
[unsettling music playing]

218
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,686
Agent Reyes went back…

219
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:13,107
to Damai Island to get evidence.

220
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:16,277
[unsettling music continues]

221
00:12:24,034 --> 00:12:25,911
These are the photos of the firearms

222
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,913
that Datu Rahman's group got from the sea.

223
00:12:29,665 --> 00:12:32,585
Instead of using
or selling those firearms,

224
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:34,962
they buried it in the mountains.

225
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:37,923
[in English] Now, tell me, Agent Angeles…

226
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:39,175
‪[tense music playing]

227
00:12:40,509 --> 00:12:42,678
Would a smuggler do that?

228
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:47,808
Would they bury firearms
to render them useless?

229
00:12:47,892 --> 00:12:50,102
[dramatic sting]

230
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:03,657
‪[dramatic sting]

231
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:14,418
[melancholic music playing]

232
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:39,068
[somber music playing]

233
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,364
‪[birds chirping]

234
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:47,576
‪[dramatic whizzing]

235
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:25,281
[somber music continues]

236
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:58,439
It's confirmed.

237
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:03,485
[morose music playing]

238
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:05,237
[in English] Marcus was up to something.

239
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,532
He didn't tell me.

240
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:13,746
You know what to do.

241
00:15:16,957 --> 00:15:20,294
But, Felix, make sure
that no one gets hurt, okay?

242
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:23,172
No one should die.

243
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:26,467
[in English] Do you understand?

244
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,764
[in English] Understood, madam.

245
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,434
‪[music intensifies]

246
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:39,104
[music fades]

247
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:45,653
[waves lapping]

248
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,785
[gloomy music playing]

249
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:31,407
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil!</i>

250
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,451
- [Jalil] <i>Jamilah!</i>
- [Jamilah giggles]

251
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:37,371
- [nostalgic music playing]
- [waves lapping gently]

252
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:45,713
[Datu Rahman] <i>Jalil.</i>

253
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:48,465
[Jalil] <i>Father.</i>

254
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:53,220
[gloomy music playing]

255
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:05,941
[somber music playing]

256
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,834
Jalil!

257
00:17:32,634 --> 00:17:34,053
Jalil!

258
00:17:35,804 --> 00:17:37,056
[sniffles]

259
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:42,269
[somber music playing]

260
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:45,773
[sniffles, sobs]

261
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:53,072
[Aminah] Jalil! Jalil!

262
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,656
[In Arabic] Praise be to God!

263
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:55,949
You're finally here!

264
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,534
Auntie.

265
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:59,328
Jalil!

266
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:02,372
[

267
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:08,712
[sobs softly, sniffles]

268
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:14,009
[somber music swells]

269
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:32,319
[music fades]

270
00:18:32,903 --> 00:18:33,737
Jalil.

271
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:39,284
[Jalil sighs]

272
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:45,749
[brooding music playing]

273
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:24,121
[music intensifies, then fades]

274
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:26,665
[Aminah] I almost didn't recognize you.

275
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:28,876
You look so different now.

276
00:19:29,459 --> 00:19:32,921
We saw Datu Rahman
on the news, by the way.

277
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:36,800
Is it true he surrendered
to Ahmad Mustapha?

278
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,678
How is he doing over there?

279
00:19:39,761 --> 00:19:41,805
Don't worry about Father, okay?

280
00:19:41,889 --> 00:19:42,764
He's safe now.

281
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:46,518
He didn't make this choice lightly.

282
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,645
He knows this is best for everyone.

283
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:50,272
[In Arabic] Praise be to God.

284
00:19:50,355 --> 00:19:52,524
That's good to hear.

285
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:54,902
What about you all?

286
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,362
How have you been here?

287
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:02,576
So much has changed, Jalil, ever since…

288
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:04,369
that night…

289
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:06,413
[scoffs]

290
00:20:06,496 --> 00:20:10,125
Especially after Datu Rahman was arrested.

291
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:14,129
And then you and Jamilah
left for Manila too.

292
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:16,256
[woman sobs]

293
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:19,259
[woman] We're all so terrified.

294
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:22,679
Even the kids around here

295
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:26,266
won't go out to play anymore.

296
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,185
[woman sobs]

297
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:30,479
It's just way too scary.

298
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:35,067
We always worry that maybe…

299
00:20:36,109 --> 00:20:41,698
what happened could happen again,

300
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:45,786
and that we won't have you
and your father here

301
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:48,830
to protect the island.

302
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:52,125
Don't worry.

303
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,087
I won't let that happen again.

304
00:20:55,170 --> 00:20:58,799
[somber music playing]

305
00:20:58,882 --> 00:21:01,260
You don't have to say that, Jalil.

306
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:04,221
We know you'll never abandon us.

307
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:09,601
But there's something worse going on.

308
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:11,812
What do you mean?

309
00:21:11,895 --> 00:21:18,318
Armed men are attacking
our neighboring islands.

310
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:23,031
They rob people, and the women…

311
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:25,993
are being sold off.

312
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:29,329
[man] They don't care
who they hurt, Jalil.

313
00:21:29,413 --> 00:21:31,331
They've got way too much firepower.

314
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:36,044
All the illegal weapons
Datu Rahman used to seize

315
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,088
are everywhere now.

316
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:40,632
[In Tausug] I'm sorry…

317
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:43,176
I couldn't get back here right away.

318
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:47,139
I'm still trying to get Father back.

319
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:52,352
I'm also looking for whoever's
behind all this chaos,

320
00:21:52,894 --> 00:21:54,438
so they can pay for what they did.

321
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:58,108
[somber music resumes]

322
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,693
[In Tausug] I'm sorry.

323
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:01,778
[In Tausug] What are you talking about?

324
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:04,156
You don't have to apologize for anything.

325
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:07,659
The most important thing is you're back,

326
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,370
and we have someone to protect the island.

327
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:17,044
[somber music continues, then fades]

328
00:22:27,137 --> 00:22:29,389
[dark music playing]

329
00:22:29,473 --> 00:22:31,224
[line ringing]

330
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:32,726
Boss.

331
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:36,772
Head to Damai Island.

332
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:42,402
Get all the weapons Datu Rahman hid there.

333
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:44,696
[Felix] <i>After that…</i>

334
00:22:46,948 --> 00:22:49,701
Kill every single person left there.

335
00:22:50,368 --> 00:22:51,578
You got that?

336
00:22:53,121 --> 00:22:54,372
Copy that, boss.

337
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:56,500
I'll send my men over now.

338
00:22:56,583 --> 00:23:00,170
[dark music continues]

339
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:10,388
[Felix] <i>This is my revenge</i>
<i>on you, Jalil Abubakar.</i>

340
00:23:14,184 --> 00:23:17,979
[music intensifies]

341
00:23:24,653 --> 00:23:26,988
NEXT ON BLOOD VS DUTY

342
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:28,990
[Lara] <i>Where's Marcus? And where's Espina?</i>

343
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:31,493
- [Felix] <i>They left already.</i>
- [Lara] <i>They're up to something.</i>

344
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:34,871
Is it really true we can take
this straight to the NLEA?

345
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:36,623
I trust him.

346
00:23:36,706 --> 00:23:40,085
My grandson died
while he was doing his job.

347
00:23:40,168 --> 00:23:42,879
It happened because of people
he thought were on his side.

348
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,714
That's why I'm here.

349
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:46,508
[Marcus] <i>There's something</i>
<i>you need to know.</i>

350
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:47,968
[suspenseful music playing]

351
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:52,597
[Jalil] <i>I never wanted any of you</i>
<i>to get hurt or die.</i>

352
00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:54,015
[Young Jalil] Father!

353
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:55,308
[Datu Rahman] There's a time to fight,

354
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:56,977
and there's a time for diplomacy.

355
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:59,604
[Jalil] <i>You never</i>
<i>made me feel like an outsider.</i>

356
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:01,857
<i>You treated me like family.</i>

357
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:05,777
[Young Jamilah] <i>Don't you miss</i>
<i>your real mom?</i>

358
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:06,945
[Jalil] I don't even
remember them, honestly.

359
00:24:07,612 --> 00:24:09,239
[Jalil] <i>Forgive me.</i>

360
00:24:09,322 --> 00:24:12,159
<i>I'm also looking for whoever's</i>
<i>behind all this chaos.</i>

361
00:24:12,242 --> 00:24:17,664
Armed men are attacking
our neighboring islands.

362
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:21,418
You're back, and we have
someone to protect the island.

363
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:31,386
BLOOD VS DUTY
